observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed to direct the Acting Municipal Accountant to;
a) Check the supporting documents for the basis in recording the transactions to their appropriate account to avoid erroneous entries.
b) Draw the necessary adjusting entries;

We recommended and Management agreed to direct the MDRRM Officer to;
a) Update themselves to the latest policies and guidelines on Donations In-Kind as provided by the relevant and competent government offices.
b) Ensure the one-time preparation and submission of the Report of the Donations, Received, Distributed and Balances to the Office of the Civil Defense and Auditor’s Office, in compliance to Item II (b) of COA Circular No. 2020-009 dated April 21, 2020 to ensure transparency on the use of these additional public funds.

We recommended and Management agreed to;
To update and finalize the Inventory Committee, who are temporarily relieved of all their regular duties, to complete the physical inventory in (3) three months or less,
To finalize the RPCPPE for CY 2021 and submit it in the Office of the Auditor which will be the basis by the Inventory Committee for preparing the Physical Inventory Plan (PIP) and;
To revise and finalize the approved Physical Inventory Plan (PIP) to the Office of the Auditor at least ten (10) calendar days before the scheduled start of the inventory-taking activities, and ensure implementation of “One-time cleansing of PPE accounts” pursuant to COA Circular 2020-006.

We recommended and Management agreed to;

a.	Direct its Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) to submit copies of the contracts enumerated above to the Office of the Auditor for the conduct of the auditorial and technical review.

b.	Instruct the BAC to strictly adhere to the provisions of item 3.1.1 of COA Circular No. 2009-001 on the submission of copies of government contracts, purchase orders, and their supporting documents to the Commission on Audit.

We recommended and Management agreed to instruct the Acting Municipal Accountant to;

a.	See to it that transactions are properly recorded in accordance with of Section 128, 131 and 137 of Volume I of GAM for LGUs to obtain reasonable assurance that the financial statements of the Municipality are fairly presented.

b.	Draw the proposed adjusting entries to correct the errors made.

We recommended and Management agreed to;
Direct its Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) to submit copies of the contracts enumerated above to the Office of the Auditor for the conduct of the auditorial and technical review.
Instruct the BAC to strictly adhere to the provisions of item 3.1.1 of COA Circular No. 2009-001 on the submission of copies of government contracts, purchase orders, and their supporting documents to the Commission on Audit.

We recommended and Management agreed to instruct the Acting Municipal Accountant to;
See to it that transactions are properly recorded in accordance with of Section 128, 131 and 137 of Volume I of GAM for LGUs to obtain reasonable assurance that the financial statements of the Municipality are fairly presented.
Draw the proposed adjusting entries to correct the errors made;

We recommended management to:
Strictly adhere COA Circular No. 97-002 in granting and utilizing cash advances;
Require the concerned Accountable Officers to liquidate their cash advances within the prescribe period as soon as the purposes for which these were granted had been served;
Reclassify the outstanding cash advances pertaining to separated/transferred officials to other receivables;
Exhaust all efforts in the retrieval and completion of the documents relative to the long outstanding cash advances; and
Ensure that all cash advances shall be fully liquidated at the end of each year.

